<Page x:Class="AsynAwaitExamples.Steps.Step18_AsyncDisposable"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:AsynAwaitExamples.ViewModels"
      Title="Step 18 - Async Disposable">
    <Page.DataContext>
        <vm:Step18ViewModel/>
    </Page.DataContext>
    <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
        <StackPanel Margin="10">
            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HeaderStyle}" 
                       Text="Step 18: Async Disposal (IAsyncDisposable)"/>

            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource ExplanationStyle}" xml:space="preserve">ASYNC DISPOSAL: Cleaning up resources that require async operations.

Regular "using" calls Dispose() synchronously. But sometimes cleanup
needs async work: flushing a network stream, closing a database connection
gracefully, sending a "goodbye" message over a socket.

IAsyncDisposable defines: ValueTask DisposeAsync()
Use "await using" instead of "using" to call it automatically.

RULE: If your class holds async resources, implement IAsyncDisposable.
The "await using" ensures DisposeAsync is called even if exceptions occur.</TextBlock>

            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? Basic 'await using'"
                    Command="{Binding BasicAwaitUsingCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? Multiple async resources"
                    Command="{Binding MultipleResourcesCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? Without await using (resource leak risk)"
                    Command="{Binding WithoutAwaitUsingCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="?? Show implementation pattern"
                    Command="{Binding ShowPatternCommand}"/>

            <TextBox Style="{StaticResource OutputStyle}" Height="280"
                     Text="{Binding OutputText, Mode=OneWay}"/>
        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Page>
